==English==
===Noun===
'''connotation''' (''plural'' '''connotations''')

# A [[meaning]] that is [[suggest]]ed or [[implied]], as opposed to a [[denotation]], or [[literal]] [[definition]]. A [[characteristic]] of [[word]]s or [[phrase]]s, or of the [[context]]s that words and phrases are used in.

====Examples====
* The '''connotations''' of the phrase "you are a [[dog]]" are that you are [[physical]]ly [[ugly]] or [[moral]]ly [[reprehensible]], not that you are a [[canine]].

